Cylinder

1. Inspect the cylinder wall for obvious scratches, unevenness, or bulges. If the cylinder is excessively rough, has deep scratches, or significant unevenness, replace the crankcase.

2. As shown in the figure, use a cylinder gauge to measure the cylinder at two directions and three positions (6 mm, 60 mm, and 110 mm from the top surface of the cylinder block). Replace the crankcase if any of the following dimensions exceed tolerance:

- Cylinder bore diameter exceeds tolerance.
- Deviation in roundness or cylindricity at two positions exceeds tolerance.
- Thrust and axial measurement deviation exceeds the roundness range.

Cylinder bore diameter limit: Φ86.02 mm;
Cylindricity limit: 0.008 mm;
Roundness limit: 0.006 mm;

Disassembly

1. Remove the fuel filler cap; refer to the disassembly procedure for the fuel tank filler cap assembly;

2. Remove the bolt at the fuel filler location;
Torque: 9 ± 3 N·m

3. Lift the vehicle;

4. Remove the rear wheel arch liner;

5. Disconnect the fuel filler hose and vent hose, charcoal canister vent hose, and the connection between the fuel filler pipe and the rear floor panel;
Fuel filler hose torque: 5 ± 0.5 N·m
Fuel filler pipe to rear floor panel torque: 15 ± 3 N·m

Disassembly

1. Drain the fuel; refer to the fuel system fuel draining procedure;
2. Remove the fuel pump wiring harness connector; refer to the fuel pump and bracket assembly disassembly procedure;
3. Disconnect the fuel filler pipe from the fuel tank fuel filler hose and vent hose;
Fuel filler hose torque: 5 ± 0.5 N·m

4. Disconnect the charcoal canister adsorption hose and carbon canister vent tube II from the charcoal canister;

Disassembly

6. Use a flat jack to support the fuel tank;
Warning: Support the bottom of the fuel tank with appropriate material to prevent damage;

Fuel pump and bracket assembly

3. Use a special tool to remove the locking nut;

4. Remove the fuel pump and bracket assembly;

Disassembly

1. Depressurize the fuel system, refer to the fuel system depressurization procedure;
2. Lift the vehicle;
3. Remove the fuel supply and return line fittings connected to the filter; refer to the quick-disconnect nylon tube fitting removal procedure for disassembly guidance;

4. Remove the filter mounting bolt and ground wire bolt;
Torque: 9 ± 3 N·m

Disassembly

1. Depressurize the fuel system, refer to the fuel system depressurization procedure;
2. Drain the fuel, refer to the fuel system draining procedure;
3. Remove the fuel tank assembly;
4. Disconnect the fuel supply and return lines from the fuel pump, refer to the quick-connect fitting disassembly procedure for nylon tubing; disconnect the connection to the fuel tank clamp;

4. Disconnect the fuel line and return line fittings connected to the filter, refer to the quick-connect fitting disassembly procedure for nylon tubing;

Disassembly

8. Lower the vehicle;

9. In the engine compartment, remove the fuel supply hose from the fuel rail fitting; refer to the nylon tube quick-connect fitting disassembly procedure for details on removing the fitting; disconnect the nylon fuel supply hose assembly from the hose clamp;

Installation

The installation process is the reverse of the disassembly process.

Disassembly

1. Disconnect the carbon canister adsorption hose, desorption hose assembly I, carbon canister vent hose I, and their connections to the carbon canister; disconnect the carbon canister adsorption hose from the adsorption tube on the fuel tank;

2. Remove the fuel tank; refer to the fuel tank assembly disassembly procedure;

3. Disconnect the connection between the desorption rigid hose assembly and the desorption hose assembly I; disconnect the connection between carbon canister vent hose I and carbon canister vent tube II;

Disassembly

6. Lower the vehicle;

7. In the engine compartment, disconnect the purge valve connector hose assembly, the charcoal canister check valve vent hose assembly, and the connection to the charcoal canister control valve;

Three-pedal assembly

13. Remove the accelerator pedal.

Remove the 3 throttle pedal mounting nuts;

For the AT brake pedal switch:

Before installing the switch, ensure that the brake pedal, master cylinder with vacuum booster assembly, are already mounted on the vehicle body, and that the pushrod fork is connected to the brake pedal arm hole using a lock pin. Ensure the pedal is in its initial position, then insert the switch into the mounting hole. Once the switch mounting surface is flush against the pedal bracket surface, rotate the switch counterclockwise by 45° until you hear a distinct "click," indicating it is properly installed.

Note:

a. Insertion direction is unique;
b. The brake pedal arm must be in a free state—do not manually interfere with its position;
c. At this point, the brake light switch contact (switch plunger) is pre-compressed by the switch stop block;
d. Be sure to rotate counterclockwise—rotating clockwise may cause damage to the brake light switch.
